"id":"mk19_bb_cv_s23",
"title":{
"__html":"Aortic Regurgitation"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"035ea8",
"children":[
"Aortic Regurgitation"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_cv_s23_1",
"title":{
"__html":"Diagnosis"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"523223",
"children":[
"Diagnosis"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"afb5a7",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"aortic regurgitation; absolute risk",
"children":[
"AR"
]
},
" is classified as chronic or acute. Acute severe AR usually is caused by ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"infective endocarditis",
"children":[
"IE"
]
},
" or aortic dissection. Chronic severe AR is most commonly associated with dilated ascending aorta from hypertension or primary aortic disease, calcific ",
{
"type":"no-wrap",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"aortic stenosis",
"children":[
"AS"
]
},
","
]
},
" bicuspid aortic valve, or rheumatic disease. Findings in chronic severe AR include:"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"8dd44e",
"children":[
"angina, orthopnea, and exertional dyspnea"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"ffcc45",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"alert",
"children":[
"widened pulse pressure"
]
},
" "
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"88ac3c",
"children":[
"left axis deviation and ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"left ventricular hypertrophy",
"children":[
"LVH"
]
},
" on ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"electrocardiogram",
"children":[
"ECG"
]
}
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"409578",
"children":[
"cardiomegaly and aortic root dilatation and calcification on chest x-ray"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"1cd76e",
"children":[
"Acute AR is associated with a short, soft, and sometimes inaudible diastolic murmur and normal heart size and pulse pressure."
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_cv_s23_2",
"title":{
"__html":"Treatment"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"4c4ac0",
"children":[
"Treatment"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"6bde31",
"children":[
{
"type":"alert",
"children":[
"Schedule immediate aortic valve replacement for patients with acute AR."
]
},
" Bridging medical therapy includes sodium nitroprusside and IV diuretics."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"628d26",
"children":[
"Indications for open surgical valve replacement:"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"6a3201",
"children":[
"symptoms (dyspnea, angina)"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"9f90e3",
"children":[
"left ventricular ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"ejection fraction",
"children":[
"EF"
]
},
" ≤55%"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"90d9fd",
"children":[
"undergoing other cardiac surgery"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"f5575e",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"transcatheter aortic valve implantation",
"children":[
"TAVI"
]
},
" is effective in select symptomatic patients who are not surgical candidates."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"258d75",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"angiotensin-converting enzyme",
"children":[
"ACE"
]
},
" inhibitors or ",
{
"type":"no-wrap",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"angiotensin receptor blocker",
"children":[
"ARB"
]
},
"s"
]
},
" and nifedipine may be used in patients with chronic AR and hypertension."
]
},
{
"type":"heading",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
"Don't Be Tricked"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"4dc6e8",
"children":[
"Do not select β-blockers or intra-aortic balloon pumps for patients with acute AR, because both may worsen the AR."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"30917d",
"children":[
"Therapy with ACE inhibitors or calcium channel blockers does not delay the need for surgery in asymptomatic patients with chronic AR."
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_cv_s23_3",
"title":{
"__html":"Follow-up"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"b9c20d",
"children":[
"Follow-up"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"9add0b",
"children":[
"Recommended follow-up involves obtaining history and physical examination, focusing on findings consistent with ",
{
"type":"no-wrap",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"heart failure",
"children":[
"HF"
]
},
","
]
},
" and performing serial echocardiography (",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"transthoracic echocardiography",
"children":[
"TTE"
]
},
"), with intervals determined by AR severity (mild, moderate, or severe)."
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_cv_s23_4",
"title":{
"__html":"Test Yourself"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"7866cc",
"children":[
"Test Yourself"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"0760a0",
"class":"test",
"children":[
"A 36-year-old man with aortic valve endocarditis is transferred to the ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"intensive care unit",
"children":[
"ICU"
]
},
" because of the abrupt onset of hypotension and hypoxemia. Physical examination findings include a ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"blood pressure",
"children":[
"BP"
]
},
" of 80/30 mm Hg, ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"hazard ratio; heart rate",
"children":[
"HR"
]
},
" of 120/min, bilateral crackles, and a gallop. No murmurs are heard."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"f9bdb1",
"class":"test_answer",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Answer:"
]
},
" ",
"For diagnosis, choose acute AR. For management, select echocardiography, IV sodium nitroprusside, and dobutamine as a bridge to urgent surgery."
]
}
]
}
]
},
